byline.original: By LIAM STACK and GABRIEL FISHER

abstract: Princeton University administrators sign document at behest of student protesters to commit to examination of racial tension on campus, ending 32-hour sit-in in university president's office; document also suggests possibility of removing name of former Pres Woodrow Wilson from public spaces on campus, citing Wilson's legacy of racism.
lead_paragraph: Students ended a 32-hour sit-in that started amid racial tension and focused on the use of former President Woodrow Wilson’s name in the university’s public spaces.

headline.main: Princeton Agrees to Consider Removing a President’s Name
